VERY LITTLE TECH STUFF -

               Two years ago when I first made an IB demo the program was
               very small, it had 32 colors, 4 levels (containing 4 screens
               each.), and 6 tiny MINDLESS enemies (per level).

               For the 1995-96 Iceburg(tm), I've overhauled the whole thing!

               It's ALL new except for the main character graphics and a few
               of the landscape graphics.

               Each level can have up to 64 screens and they are drawn in
               64 color half-brite mode.

               The enemies are not quite as mindless as the 1992-93 guys
               were, some of these new guys travel in little boats and
               others will even shoot at you!

               The screen redrawing in this IB is VERY much an improvement
               over the "old" IB, I used to have a lot of redraw errors
               like the one I've already mentioned, not only the gems, but
               almost all the objects on the screen wouldn't redraw
               correctly.

               I would have a screen full of flashing/half drawn
               objects, very annoying!! The redrawing is up to about 96%
               error-free. (I'm not going to lose anymore time on trying to
               get it perfect until I'm finished with the game. Update?)

